1
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:03,750
Sui.

2
00:00:05,220 --> 00:00:09,030
Want to pick up where we left off that night?

3
00:00:30,460 --> 00:00:32,070
Sorry.

4
00:00:34,640 --> 00:00:38,200
You drank too much.

5
00:00:39,020 --> 00:00:41,760
Rest up, okay?

6
00:00:41,760 --> 00:00:43,450
Good night.

7
00:02:05,970 --> 00:02:07,770
They were considering this one.

8
00:02:07,770 --> 00:02:09,870
I see.

9
00:02:09,870 --> 00:02:13,120
- Nothing beats a simple design.
- Hello.

10
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:14,910
- Hello.
- Hello there.

11
00:02:14,910 --> 00:02:16,760
- Come on in.
- Don't wanna!

12
00:02:16,760 --> 00:02:18,670
- Nice to meet you.
- Show them inside.

13
00:02:18,670 --> 00:02:19,610
Right.

14
00:02:19,610 --> 00:02:21,570
- Thanks for having us.
- Of course.

15
00:02:21,570 --> 00:02:24,420
- Please, have a seat.
- Thank you.

16
00:02:24,420 --> 00:02:26,480
- I wanna go home!
- Monou.

17
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:29,130
Could you grab drinks for them?

18
00:02:29,130 --> 00:02:30,510
I need to take this call.

19
00:02:30,510 --> 00:02:31,950
I'm on it.

20
00:02:31,950 --> 00:02:34,300
Thank you.

21
00:02:34,300 --> 00:02:36,610
Yes, thank you for calling.

22
00:02:37,810 --> 00:02:40,730
Excuse me...

23
00:02:40,730 --> 00:02:44,110
And cross. That's it.

24
00:02:44,110 --> 00:02:45,960
All right.

25
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:47,680
Let me get to work.

26
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:49,410
- I'm sorry about him.
- No worries.

27
00:02:49,410 --> 00:02:50,980
Shall we get started?

28
00:02:50,980 --> 00:02:53,460
Surely not with him bothering you...

29
00:02:53,460 --> 00:02:55,420
He's no bother at all.

30
00:02:56,230 --> 00:02:58,150
First thing on the docket

31
00:02:58,150 --> 00:03:01,540
would be the flooring we recommended.

32
00:03:01,540 --> 00:03:03,410
Seeing as your child is still young...

33
00:03:03,410 --> 00:03:07,170
All right, thank you again.

34
00:03:07,990 --> 00:03:09,450
Thanks for the help.

35
00:03:09,450 --> 00:03:11,270
No worries at all.

36
00:03:13,410 --> 00:03:17,230
Mao's a real sucker for kids, isn't he?

37
00:03:17,230 --> 00:03:19,760
I had no idea. I was so surprised.

38
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:23,460
He's not friendly,
so why do they all love him?

39
00:03:23,460 --> 00:03:27,200
Kids can tell Mao's a nice guy.

40
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:31,580
I guess my kindness is too difficult
for kids to understand.

41
00:03:37,100 --> 00:03:39,210
Your phone is ringing.

42
00:03:47,810 --> 00:03:51,160
I'll call them back later.

43
00:04:03,980 --> 00:04:06,190
It must be urgent.

44
00:04:06,190 --> 00:04:08,290
I'll have to take this.

45
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:13,260
One step, two step...

46
00:04:13,260 --> 00:04:15,570
- It was great talking with you.
- Likewise.

47
00:04:15,570 --> 00:04:16,730
I apologize it took so long.

48
00:04:16,730 --> 00:04:18,770
No, thank you for handling him.

49
00:04:18,770 --> 00:04:20,730
Come on, we're leaving.

50
00:04:20,730 --> 00:04:25,500
Don't wanna. I'm staying with big brother.

51
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:27,760
Thank you for your time today.

52
00:04:27,760 --> 00:04:30,290
No, thank you.

53
00:04:30,290 --> 00:04:33,130
You were very patient today.

54
00:04:33,130 --> 00:04:34,470
Want a lollipop?

55
00:04:34,470 --> 00:04:35,630
Thank you!

56
00:04:35,630 --> 00:04:37,520
You like it?

57
00:04:37,520 --> 00:04:38,950
- Yeah!
- I'm glad.

58
00:04:38,950 --> 00:04:41,980
- But no eating it yet.
- Yeah, not with the wrapper.

59
00:04:41,980 --> 00:04:44,290
What flavor is it?

60
00:04:44,290 --> 00:04:46,370
- I think it's orange.
- Do you like orange?

61
00:04:46,370 --> 00:04:48,580
- Yup!
- Awesome.

62
00:04:49,940 --> 00:04:52,680
Want me to open that for you?

63
00:04:55,470 --> 00:04:59,150
Your place lives up to all expectations, Mao.

64
00:04:59,150 --> 00:05:02,990
Hey, no snooping around.

65
00:05:02,990 --> 00:05:05,330
It's so stylish in here.

66
00:05:05,330 --> 00:05:06,630
You're exaggerating.

67
00:05:06,630 --> 00:05:12,120
I'm really not,
given the rooms of most single guys.

68
00:05:12,120 --> 00:05:13,920
That's enough of that.

69
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:17,740
Here's to Monou joining our team at Idea.

70
00:05:17,740 --> 00:05:20,430
- Cheers!
- Cheers.

71
00:05:20,430 --> 00:05:22,590
Have you gotten used to the work yet?

72
00:05:22,590 --> 00:05:25,410
Only thanks to you all.

73
00:05:25,410 --> 00:05:28,090
You're also a quick learner, Monou.

74
00:05:28,090 --> 00:05:32,100
The Hayase's already trust you
with their kitchen.

75
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:35,610
Knowing how to cater to every client's needs

76
00:05:35,610 --> 00:05:39,880
has certainly been a learning experience.

77
00:05:39,880 --> 00:05:43,680
A struggle our local chatterbox, Matsubara,
probably can't relate to.

78
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:47,280
Hey, it's only because I have my methods.

79
00:05:47,280 --> 00:05:49,810
For example, check this out.

80
00:05:49,810 --> 00:05:52,030
[Life Planning App]

81
00:05:52,030 --> 00:05:54,350
A life planning app?

82
00:05:54,350 --> 00:05:58,640
Doing this together
gets my clients to open up,

83
00:05:58,640 --> 00:06:02,360
and acts as a great icebreaker.

84
00:06:04,020 --> 00:06:06,550
You're actually giving legit advice for once.

85
00:06:06,550 --> 00:06:11,480
If you doubt me, why not give it a shot?

86
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:13,920
Forcing that onto us isn't appropriate.

87
00:06:13,920 --> 00:06:16,640
Aw, bummer.

88
00:06:16,640 --> 00:06:20,530
I wanted to learn more about you.

89
00:06:20,530 --> 00:06:23,370
I'll just direct my questions
toward Mao instead.

90
00:06:27,790 --> 00:06:30,900
Mao isn't interested in your interrogation.

91
00:06:30,900 --> 00:06:32,660
I don't mind.

92
00:06:32,660 --> 00:06:34,640
Awesome.

93
00:06:34,640 --> 00:06:36,610
Then here I go.

94
00:06:36,610 --> 00:06:39,810
Question one. "Are you married?"

95
00:06:39,810 --> 00:06:42,390
I know that's a "no," so onto question two.

96
00:06:42,390 --> 00:06:46,090
Question two. "Do you want to get married?"

97
00:06:46,090 --> 00:06:48,240
I guess.

98
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:51,530
Question three. "Do you have a partner?"

99
00:06:51,530 --> 00:06:52,940
I don't.

100
00:06:52,940 --> 00:06:54,420
Then that's a "no".

101
00:06:54,420 --> 00:06:59,750
Question four. "Do you have anyone you like?"

102
00:07:07,810 --> 00:07:09,420
I do.

103
00:07:10,150 --> 00:07:11,610
What?

104
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:21,120
Those are the omelettes.

105
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:22,180
I'll grab them.

106
00:07:22,180 --> 00:07:23,470
It's fine, it's your party.

107
00:07:23,470 --> 00:07:25,970
I'd feel bad just sitting around.

108
00:07:25,970 --> 00:07:28,090
- Then could you grab the plates?
- Sure.

109
00:07:29,980 --> 00:07:32,620
It just split in half.

110
00:07:33,730 --> 00:07:36,470
- Is it too hot?
- Nope.

111
00:07:39,670 --> 00:07:41,240
Sorry to go without cleaning up.

112
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:45,060
Don't worry about it.
You two have last trains to catch.

113
00:07:45,060 --> 00:07:46,990
We'll tidy up the rest.

114
00:07:46,990 --> 00:07:48,940
Thank you.

115
00:07:48,940 --> 00:07:50,810
- See you at work.
- See you.

116
00:07:50,810 --> 00:07:52,060
Thanks for having us.

117
00:07:52,060 --> 00:07:53,190
Sure.

118
00:07:53,190 --> 00:07:55,070
Good night.

119
00:07:57,990 --> 00:08:00,210
I'll get that.

120
00:08:00,210 --> 00:08:02,550
Thanks.

121
00:08:02,550 --> 00:08:04,740
No, thanks for helping out,

122
00:08:04,740 --> 00:08:07,890
even though it was your party.

123
00:08:07,890 --> 00:08:09,800
Don't worry about it.

124
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:13,140
I prefer to keep busy.

125
00:08:15,100 --> 00:08:16,400
So...

126
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:17,990
Yeah?

127
00:08:17,990 --> 00:08:20,150
How have things been?

128
00:08:20,150 --> 00:08:22,080
Huh?

129
00:08:22,080 --> 00:08:24,170
You know,

130
00:08:24,170 --> 00:08:26,250
with Mr. Hirose and the presentation.

131
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:31,280
I'm editing my proposal

132
00:08:31,280 --> 00:08:36,040
until I get a favorable response from him.

133
00:08:36,040 --> 00:08:38,250
I see.

134
00:08:38,250 --> 00:08:41,470
I figured this wouldn't be easy.

135
00:08:41,470 --> 00:08:46,860
If anything, I appreciate the challenge
he's set out for me.

136
00:08:49,110 --> 00:08:52,480
He was already pretty famous
by the time I was a student.

137
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:56,520
But he really is amazing, isn't he?

138
00:08:58,420 --> 00:08:59,960
Yeah.

139
00:09:03,650 --> 00:09:05,680
So you agree?

140
00:09:07,290 --> 00:09:08,700
Huh?

141
00:09:09,510 --> 00:09:11,550
No, it's just...

142
00:09:11,550 --> 00:09:16,030
After speaking to someone you admire,
don't you find yourself falling for them?

143
00:09:19,740 --> 00:09:24,520
Admiration and romance
are two different things.

144
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:30,090
They can sometimes overlap, right?

145
00:09:31,510 --> 00:09:35,580
Maybe. Except, Mr. Hirose is married.

146
00:09:35,580 --> 00:09:38,340
I know, but...

147
00:09:38,340 --> 00:09:42,580
People like him have partners
who are on their equal footing.

148
00:09:45,680 --> 00:09:50,060
You don't plan on dating anyone these days?

149
00:09:52,250 --> 00:09:53,760
Nope.

150
00:09:55,980 --> 00:09:59,420
Even if someone confessed their love to you?

151
00:10:02,490 --> 00:10:03,990
Even then.

152
00:10:05,460 --> 00:10:09,810
For now, I'd rather focus on
making do on my own.

153
00:10:18,620 --> 00:10:20,940
That's the girl who's quitting.

154
00:10:20,940 --> 00:10:22,350
Seriously? Was she fired?

155
00:10:22,350 --> 00:10:23,770
Apparently.

156
00:10:23,770 --> 00:10:26,410
Yikes. How'd that happen?

157
00:10:38,430 --> 00:10:41,480
<i>The person you have called
is currently unavailable.</i>

158
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:44,030
<i>Please leave a message after the...</i>

159
00:10:55,190 --> 00:10:57,310
Please excuse the noise.

160
00:11:04,970 --> 00:11:09,360
I'm sorry for inviting you out
when you're so busy.

161
00:11:09,360 --> 00:11:13,120
Don't worry, I was getting hungry anyway.

162
00:11:19,920 --> 00:11:26,510
Are you still being followed around?

163
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:32,630
Not for now.
I've also informed our boss about it.

164
00:11:32,630 --> 00:11:34,440
That's great to hear.

165
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:37,120
Your lunch sets.

166
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:38,920
Thank you.

167
00:11:38,920 --> 00:11:40,870
Thank you.

168
00:11:42,520 --> 00:11:44,160
Looks delicious!

169
00:11:49,870 --> 00:11:51,500
Monou.

170
00:11:53,230 --> 00:11:59,190
I think you're a wonderful person.

171
00:11:59,190 --> 00:12:00,970
What?

172
00:12:00,970 --> 00:12:03,990
You even worry for me
and my circumstances.

173
00:12:06,130 --> 00:12:08,020
But, well...

174
00:12:09,240 --> 00:12:12,550
The thing is...

175
00:12:14,430 --> 00:12:15,950
Yes?

176
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:28,300
What do you think of Mao?

177
00:12:32,970 --> 00:12:34,650
Pardon?

178
00:12:37,550 --> 00:12:40,260
Who do you think

179
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:43,580
is the person Mao loves?

180
00:12:46,270 --> 00:12:50,840
I've only had eyes for Mao.

181
00:12:52,050 --> 00:12:53,910
That's why, I...

182
00:12:55,950 --> 00:12:57,720
I...

183
00:13:01,670 --> 00:13:03,450
Mizuno.

184
00:13:04,740 --> 00:13:10,710
I think you're perfect for Mao.

185
00:13:14,630 --> 00:13:19,280
I plan to root for you all the way.

186
00:13:24,990 --> 00:13:27,330
Thank you.

187
00:13:31,520 --> 00:13:34,520
Are you looking for Imamura's past works?

188
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:38,850
Yes, but I'll find it myself.

189
00:13:39,560 --> 00:13:40,890
It'll be faster if I help.

190
00:13:40,890 --> 00:13:42,960
I got this covered, really.

191
00:13:47,430 --> 00:13:49,540
You seem angry.

192
00:13:50,980 --> 00:13:52,560
Sorry.

193
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:56,540
But I promise I'm fine.

194
00:13:58,030 --> 00:14:02,460
Don't keep Mizuno waiting, okay?

195
00:14:02,460 --> 00:14:04,250
She's relying on you to bring her home.

196
00:14:07,340 --> 00:14:10,210
I'm worried about you too, Sui.

197
00:14:13,950 --> 00:14:16,280
I appreciate the sentiment.

198
00:14:16,280 --> 00:14:21,030
But that kindness of yours

199
00:14:21,030 --> 00:14:23,940
can cause misunderstandings.

200
00:14:27,340 --> 00:14:32,470
If someone out there has a crush on you,

201
00:14:32,470 --> 00:14:38,180
they wouldn't want to see you
caring for me, either.

202
00:14:42,680 --> 00:14:44,200
A stalker?

203
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:45,960
Is that girl okay?

204
00:14:45,960 --> 00:14:48,830
She's already told Mr. Hoshina about it,

205
00:14:48,830 --> 00:14:53,050
and Mao's walking her home, so she's safe.

206
00:14:54,030 --> 00:14:57,240
Again with that bad habit of his? Jeez...

207
00:14:57,240 --> 00:14:58,590
Huh?

208
00:14:58,590 --> 00:15:01,440
If Mao ever sees someone in need,

209
00:15:01,440 --> 00:15:04,980
his sense of justice gets the best of him.

210
00:15:04,980 --> 00:15:06,590
I see.

211
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:12,210
Though, I suppose his upbringing is to blame,

212
00:15:12,210 --> 00:15:15,430
so I can't admonish him too much about it.

213
00:15:15,430 --> 00:15:17,060
His upbringing?

214
00:15:17,060 --> 00:15:18,400
Yeah.

215
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:20,990
The reason why my family took in Mao,

216
00:15:20,990 --> 00:15:23,270
<i>was because of his father's
violent tendencies.</i>

217
00:15:23,270 --> 00:15:26,720
Auntie? Mao?

218
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:39,870
Dear, stop this.

219
00:15:39,870 --> 00:15:41,930
Stop it!

220
00:15:43,350 --> 00:15:45,190
Quit clinging, you nuisance!

221
00:15:45,190 --> 00:15:47,580
Stop it, please!

222
00:15:49,650 --> 00:15:52,270
- Damn you.
- Stop, stop...

223
00:15:52,270 --> 00:15:54,770
<i>That troublesome habit of his came to be</i>

224
00:15:54,770 --> 00:15:58,560
because he was unable to protect his mother.

225
00:16:03,240 --> 00:16:06,610
As if a young child
could ever protect their parents.

226
00:16:15,010 --> 00:16:17,280
You ready to go, Mizuno?

227
00:16:17,280 --> 00:16:19,490
Yes. One moment.

228
00:16:23,700 --> 00:16:26,590
[Blocked Caller]

229
00:16:30,950 --> 00:16:32,720
- See you all tomorrow.
- See you.

230
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:33,980
See you guys.

231
00:16:33,980 --> 00:16:36,180
Take care.

232
00:16:46,640 --> 00:16:48,320
Mizuno?

233
00:16:49,190 --> 00:16:50,810
Mao...

234
00:16:51,990 --> 00:16:53,700
I...

235
00:16:55,410 --> 00:16:58,900
I love you.

236
00:17:01,350 --> 00:17:03,760
That was sudden.

237
00:17:03,760 --> 00:17:05,770
But it's not.

238
00:17:06,560 --> 00:17:09,370
I'm sure you've also noticed

239
00:17:09,370 --> 00:17:11,450
my feelings for you.

240
00:17:15,630 --> 00:17:19,650
I've always loved you.

241
00:17:27,100 --> 00:17:29,370
Mao.

242
00:17:29,370 --> 00:17:35,090
Will you protect me, as my boyfriend?

243
00:17:41,620 --> 00:17:44,530
- Well...
- It's fine.

244
00:17:44,530 --> 00:17:46,960
You don't need to answer me now.

245
00:17:47,580 --> 00:17:49,670
Just please,

246
00:17:49,670 --> 00:17:53,020
give it some proper thought.

247
00:17:56,530 --> 00:17:58,260
All right, I will.

248
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:02,890
You don't need to walk me any farther.

249
00:18:02,890 --> 00:18:05,140
I know you have places to be.

250
00:18:05,140 --> 00:18:08,390
- But...
- See you tomorrow.

251
00:18:18,420 --> 00:18:20,820
- Hey there.
- Welcome back.

252
00:18:25,940 --> 00:18:29,190
Huh? You're back?

253
00:18:29,190 --> 00:18:30,710
Yeah.

254
00:18:31,450 --> 00:18:33,760
What about Nana?

255
00:18:33,760 --> 00:18:37,650
She said she'd be fine,
so I came back to work overtime.

256
00:18:37,650 --> 00:18:39,590
Wait.

257
00:18:39,590 --> 00:18:42,430
You let her go home alone?

258
00:18:42,430 --> 00:18:45,350
She insisted.

259
00:18:46,150 --> 00:18:50,010
You didn't notice
something's been bothering her?

260
00:18:50,580 --> 00:18:52,710
Damn it, I should've...

261
00:18:54,690 --> 00:18:59,300
This isn't "kindness" on your part at all.

262
00:19:25,160 --> 00:19:28,200
[Just Married]

263
00:19:37,520 --> 00:19:39,280
Monou?

264
00:19:41,090 --> 00:19:43,260
Hirose.

265
00:19:43,300 --> 00:19:49,200
[Ruby on]

266
00:20:01,280 --> 00:20:02,800
You...

267
00:20:07,080 --> 00:20:09,740
Leave me alone!

268
00:20:09,740 --> 00:20:11,530
Don't come any closer!

269
00:20:11,530 --> 00:20:13,940
Please, leave me alone.

270
00:20:13,940 --> 00:20:15,910
Stop!

271
00:20:22,280 --> 00:20:23,950
[Uncle]

272
00:20:26,750 --> 00:20:28,000
Hello?

273
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:30,440
<i>Mao, where the hell are you right now?</i>

274
00:20:30,440 --> 00:20:32,630
I'm at the office.

275
00:20:32,630 --> 00:20:36,950
<i>Idiot, you didn't walk Mizuno home?</i>

276
00:20:43,550 --> 00:20:47,370
- Please wait right over here.
- Thank you.

277
00:20:52,490 --> 00:20:54,120
Are you okay?

278
00:20:56,320 --> 00:20:59,400
Yeah. It was only a slight sprain.

279
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:02,050
It looks worse than it actually is.

280
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:05,470
I'm so sorry.

281
00:21:05,470 --> 00:21:07,860
I didn't mean to get you hurt, too.

282
00:21:07,860 --> 00:21:09,580
Don't apologize.

283
00:21:09,580 --> 00:21:13,980
If you hadn't caught up,
it would have been worse.

284
00:21:18,340 --> 00:21:20,560
Thank god you're safe.

285
00:21:30,090 --> 00:21:31,770
Listen...

286
00:21:32,890 --> 00:21:37,670
Nana, I really...

287
00:21:37,670 --> 00:21:39,670
Mizuno.

288
00:21:41,790 --> 00:21:43,530
Mao?

289
00:21:44,180 --> 00:21:46,110
Mao!

290
00:21:54,270 --> 00:21:56,230
I was terrified.

291
00:21:58,190 --> 00:22:00,230
I was so, so scared.

292
00:22:04,140 --> 00:22:06,260
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

293
00:22:06,260 --> 00:22:10,360
<i>I'm sorry I couldn't protect you.</i>

294
00:22:17,460 --> 00:22:19,930
I'm sorry I left you to fend for yourself.

295
00:22:24,610 --> 00:22:26,200
Mizuno.

296
00:22:28,110 --> 00:22:31,820
My answer is yes, I'll be your boyfriend.

297
00:22:35,280 --> 00:22:36,800
What?

298
00:22:40,700 --> 00:22:43,160
Good morning.

299
00:22:47,940 --> 00:22:50,480
It was only a light sprain.

300
00:22:50,480 --> 00:22:52,210
Thank goodness.

301
00:22:52,210 --> 00:22:54,030
- Morning.
- Good morning.

302
00:22:54,030 --> 00:22:56,310
Did something happen yesterday?

303
00:22:58,390 --> 00:23:02,610
Nana was almost assaulted on her way home.

304
00:23:02,610 --> 00:23:04,100
What?

305
00:23:05,870 --> 00:23:10,720
Mao swooped in to save her just in time.

306
00:23:11,390 --> 00:23:13,960
The stalker was her ex,

307
00:23:13,960 --> 00:23:16,400
who was finally arrested.

308
00:23:17,030 --> 00:23:21,150
I see. That's great news.

309
00:23:21,150 --> 00:23:25,440
Is it really?

310
00:23:25,440 --> 00:23:26,920
Huh?

311
00:23:28,960 --> 00:23:33,600
Those two are a couple now.

312
00:23:45,610 --> 00:23:46,960
Want me to help later?

313
00:23:46,960 --> 00:23:48,600
No, I'd like to do this on my own.

314
00:23:48,600 --> 00:23:50,920
I'm sorry I made you worry.

315
00:23:50,920 --> 00:23:53,300
I didn't wish to eat alone tonight.

316
00:23:53,300 --> 00:23:56,250
Life never quite works out
as planned, does it?

317
00:23:56,250 --> 00:24:00,000
Not every family
can be blessed with children.

